ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Highly recommended - great research class looking at the state of the art in databases.
Recommended. it's a really nice course in database and distributed system principle, with lots of practical frameworks.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course made me get familiarity with implementing a SQL database and also led me to research distributed systems in detail. It was a great complement to another class where my team was building an app with MongoDB. I hope to have a database in my dissertation, so in that sense this was a course I will benefit from going forward.
